jobs_results.title: Jr. Android Developer
jobs_results.description:
Android Developer

We are seeking highly skilled Android developers to join our team. As a key member of our development team, you will be responsible for implementing best practices in developing Android applications that target multiple devices and platform versions.
Key Responsibilities:
• Implementing best practices for developing Android applications that target multiple devices and platform versions.
• Maintaining production app's code up-to-date and bug-free.
• Conducting code reviews to minimize errors and ensure code quality.
• Collaborating with the development team to deliver valuable technical solutions.
• Staying aware and up-to-date with development standards and frameworks.
Requirements:
• Degree in software engineering or equivalent.
• 1+ years of experience within mobile development.
• Experience with Android SDK.
• Strong understanding of Android Studio IDE.
• Strong understanding of support libraries and frameworks.
• Fluent coding skill in Java.
• Proficient in XML layout building.
• Multi-threaded coding experience.
• Familiarity with REST Web Services and integration.
• Excellent communication skills, both verbal and written, including good technical writing and interpersonal skills.
• Good attention to detail and problem-solving skills, with a passion for quality and engineering excellence at scale.
Nice to Have:
• Fluency in Kotlin (Objective-C and/or Swift highly valuable).
• Understanding of design patterns and architectures (MVP and MVVM preferably).
What You Can Expect:
• Technical mentoring and leadership.
• Challenging projects to keep you at the cutting edge of tech trends.
• Cool teammates and a good work environment.

Estimated Salary: $120,000 - $180,000 per year

jobs_results.description:
About the job
• The Developer’s mission is to contribute to the functional and application related consistency of the IT solution and ensure the service continuity and continuous development
• The Developer must perform activities within the framework of projects and/or application maintenance and development seeking it’s continuous development and assuring it’s compliance with Quality and Security guidelines and best practices

Your Main Activities Are

Profile and Skills to Success
• Bachelor Degree in Information Technology / Computer Science or related
• Up to 2 years of experience in Information Technology or similar
• Advanced level of English, both written and oral
• Attention to detail / rigor
• Ability to collaborate / teamwork
• Analytical ability

#LI-Hybrid

Why joining BNP Paribas?

· Leading banking institution

BNP Paribas is the European Union’s leading bank, and key player in international banking. It operates in 63 countries and has nearly 183.000 employees, including more than 146.000 in Europe.

· Our presence in Portugal

In Portugal since 1985, BNP Paribas today has more than 8.700 employees, distributed across the Group's 10 business entities established in the country. Its presence also extends to 11 excellence centres providing value-added services to various countries where the BNP Paribas Group also operates.

· International reach

Thanks to its international presence and regular and close collaboration among its different entities, BNP Paribas has the resources to support all clients with financing, investment, savings and protection solutions that help make their projects a success. BNP Paribas holds key positions in its three core operating divisions:
• Retail Banking, a division that brings together all of the Group’s retail activities and specialised business lines;
• Investment & Protection Services that include specialised businesses offering a wide range of savings, investment and protection services;
• Corporate & Institutional Banking division that offers tailored financial solutions for corporate and institutional clients.

· Diversity and Inclusion commitment

BNP Paribas is an equal opportunity employer and proud to provide equal employment opportunity to all job seekers. We are actively committed to ensuring that no individual is discriminated against on the grounds of age, disability, gender reassignment, marriage or civil partnership status, pregnancy and maternity/paternity, race, religion or belief, sex or sexual orientation. Equity and diversity are at the core of our recruitment policy because we believe that they foster creativity and efficiency, which in turn increase performance and productivity. We strive to reflect the society we live in, while keeping with the image of our clients.

· Commitment towards work/life balance

At BNP Paribas we care about our employees wellbeing and promote a culture of good integration between work and rest. We believe our employees have rich personal lives outside of work, being fundamental to be disconnected from work to recharge both physically and mentally. Only through this balance we may all be at our best while working.

· Remote Working Conditions

At BNP Paribas, we embrace a Smart Working framework based on trust, autonomy and collaboration. Within this framework, eligible employees can benefit from flexible remote working modalities adapted to our hybrid working environment. To guarantee a comfortable and efficient working set-up, eligible employees are provided with both the office and home equipment, are entitled to an equipment allowance and can benefit from exclusive partnerships to purchase additional equipment at reduced prices.

To find out more on why you should join BNP Paribas visit https://bnpp.lk/why-BNP-Paribas-Portugal
• Please note that only applications submitted in English will be considered.
• In case you are selected for this role, further documentation will be requested to support your hiring process.

jobs_results.title: Mobile Developer (Android)
Mobile Developer
Senior Mobile Developer (RN, iOS, Android)
jobs_results.description: Since 2015 Sweatcoin and now Sweat Economy is working on making the world more physically active. With more than 100 million registered users, thousands of partners and a proven ability to make people move more (+20%) Sweat Economy has already become the largest onramp in web3 history. We now working on turning our token - $SWEAT - into the principal unit of physical activity value and building an economy of movement around it. As a Senior Mobile Developer, you will contribute the team for making the Sweat Wallet app into the best multichain mobile wallet on the market with tens of millions of users. You will work on : The tasks are complex and exciting - cosmic UI, optimization of battery consumption, GPS / Motion, Anti-fraud and Security, analytics and growth & A/B testing. Most of the UI is implemented with React Native. The overall stack is Android/iOS SDK + Kotlin + Swift + React Native. Work day-to-day in a multinational cross-functional team of engineers, designers, and product managers to build the best fitness & health app Collaborate with other service teams on evolving our shared processes and tooling to support a large number of teams working on a diverse array of products Explore new ways of solving cross-platform design problems at scale Apply, if You have: Portfolio of consumer-facing high-performance mobile applications available in stores Advanced React Native skills Android SDK / Kotlin / Apple iOS SDK / Swift would be an advantage Good understanding of sensors, Google-play, Apple services Be able to write maintainable and readable code, good knowledge of design patterns Self-motivated and able to achieve deadlines and work independently English - Upper-Intermediate or above You care deeply about usability, accessibility and performance You are eager to learn new technologies (we will support you with training & mentoring) We value and pay attention to self-education and self-improvement in all areas, even not related to the profession, that is of interest to you. What you get in return: Remote-friendly & Flexible working hours. The flexibility is incredible, performance is based on output, rather than hours spent working, you can be wherever you want! Apple devices for work Team buildings abroad in exciting locations, when borders are open, we will announce the next adventure! Health insurance coverage WellBeing program, which supports up to 2 counselling sessions per month Unlimited time-off policy If you feel that's a match we would be excited to have you on our team!

jobs_results.title: Android Developer - Lisboa
jobs_results.description:
Who are we:

Neotalent Conclusion is one of the leading Iberian specialists providing services in Information Technology and Engineering services. As part of the Netherlands-based organization Conclusion, which has an ecosystem of over 25 companies and 3,600 employees, we are focused on increasing the technological capacity of our clients and the digital transformation of their application ecosystems.

We are talent specialists, attracting the best people and combining them with the needs of the most ambitious projects, at the right time. Our success comes from our investments in innovation, our focus on results, and, above all, the guarantee that our people will have happy and rewarding careers.

With over 25 years of solid experience, Neotalent Conclusion has established its presence in key locations, including Lisbon, Porto, and Madrid. The company currently has more than 950 professionals in the different areas in which it operates.

Neotalent, the responsive people.

Find out more about us at .

Role Overview:

We are looking for an Android Developer to reinforce our teams, at one of our clients, in a project to develop an open platform for the distribution and discovery of Android mobile applications, allowing users to download and upload applications and create stores to share them.

What you will do:

You will be responsible for Develop and maintain projects, collaborate with UI/UX designers to implement design, collaborate with cross-functional teams for feature integration, stay updated on Android platform changes and best practices and troubleshoot and resolve Android-specific issues.

What you are like:
• 2+ years of experience in Android Development;
• Bachelor's degree in computer science or related field.
• Proficiency in Kotlin / Java;
• Experience with Android development tools (Android Studio, SDK);
• Knowledge of Android networking and experience creating a client that communicates with the server via REST API; ideally using Retrofit, OkHttp, and Moshi (or other JSON library).
• Knowledge of Android design guidelines and best practices.
• Familiarity with asynchronous programming techniques such as Kotlin Coroutines.
• Being proficient in English.

Why join us:
• Work on challenging projects for big clients
• Learn more about emerging technologies
• Possibility of working remotely
• Design your career plan
• Access to continuous training and certifications
• Evolve through our internal mobility program
• … and much more!

To apply: Please send your CV to with PBR_Android in the email subject

jobs_results.title: Android Developer - Pain-Free World Champion
jobs_results.description:
Sword Health, a pioneering end-to-end platform for pain prediction, prevention, and treatment, is revolutionizing the healthcare landscape. Our mission is to empower two billion people worldwide by harnessing technology to reduce pain and surgery intent.

We are seeking an exceptional Android Developer to join our team of 800+ talented individuals across two continents. As a champion of innovation, you will be instrumental in building a pain-free world powered by cutting-edge technology and enhanced by human expertise, accessible to all.
• *What You'll Be Doing:**

• Drive ownership and accountability of work, delivering clear and concise communication throughout projects.

• Execute defined tasks within project scope with guidance from managers/TLs, fostering collaboration and effective teamwork.

• Contribute to problem-solving with defined solutions, embracing diverse perspectives, and providing high-quality work products.

• Develop self-awareness, understanding core processes, and actively participating in planning, on-call rotations, bug triage, metrics review, and more.

• Learn and participate in interview and recruitment processes, enhancing your skills and knowledge.

• Collaborate with the product team to define requirements and improve specifications.
• *What We Need:**

• More than 3 years of experience in developing Android Applications.

• Proficiency in Android, its lifecycle, Kotlin, Dependency Injection, REST API integration, and other essential skills.

• Good understanding of Android Components, Firebase, Crashlytics, frameworks/SDK integration, and Coroutines.

• Experience with unit tests and proficiency in Gradle.
• *Why Join Us:**

We offer a stimulating, fast-paced environment with plenty of room for creativity and growth. Enjoy a competitive salary, career development opportunities, and a chance to work with a talented team, making a real impact on innovative healthcare solutions. Work remotely or hybrid, enjoy unlimited vacation time, and access our health and well-being program.
• *Location:** Portugal. **Salary Range:** €80,000 - €120,000 per year, depending on experience.

jobs_results.title: Senior Mobile Developer (ReactNative)
jobs_results.description:
Job Description

Job description:

Join our Team as a Senior Mobile Developer and contribute to our Group's mission of delivering top-tier Craftsmen’s ERP solutions. We're looking for a passionate and experienced Mobile Developer to strengthen our Development Hub in Lisbon, that collaborates with other Group Product and Engineering Teams that together build and maintain our Group Products.

Our hybrid work setup offers flexibility, allowing you to work two days a week in the office and three days from home.

Responsibilities:
• Mentor and Tech coach a Mobile Development Team on Product Development and Maintenance activities.
• Ensure seamless integration of iOS and Android platforms, leveraging Xcode and Android Studio for app builds and deployments.
• Manage the release process to both Apple App Store and Google Play, ensuring adherence to platform guidelines and submission processes.
• Develop, enhance, and maintain cross-platform mobile applications using React Native, Redux.
• Collaborate with designers to implement intuitive and visually appealing user interfaces.
• Integrate APIs to fetch and display data in mobile applications.
• Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of the application.
• Debug and troubleshoot issues as they arise and provide timely solutions.
• Stay up-to-date with the latest trends and best practices in mobile development.

Qualifications

Skills & Requirements:
• React Native - The candidate must have strong proficiency in React Native, including a deep understanding of React Native components, navigation, state management, and third-party libraries.
• Extensive experience in publishing mobile applications to the Apple App Store and Google Play Store using Xcode and Android Studio.
• JavaScript/TypeScript - Strong knowledge and experience in JavaScript or TypeScript, including ES6+ features, syntax, and best practices for writing clean and maintainable code.
• API Integration - Experience working with APIs to fetch and manipulate data in mobile applications.
• UI/UX Design Principles - Understanding of fundamental UI/UX design principles and the ability to work closely with designers to implement visually appealing and user-friendly interfaces.
• Cross-Platform Development - Familiarity with developing cross-platform mobile applications for iOS and Android.
• Testing and Debugging - Proficiency in debugging and testing mobile applications to ensure performance and quality.
• Git and Version Control - Familiarity with Git and version control systems.
